	   <tr><td colspan=2>Although it's generally true that guilds in VT have complex point systems or award systems, people still tend to keep the good of the guild in mind.<br><br>This dropped recently in VT. A paladin bid on it. Then I bid on it, too. Then the paladin graciously withdrew, saying &quot;cleric FT4 is better than paladin FT4&quot;. He might have pressed the issue, but he certainly would have gotten ill will from a number of people.<br><br>Our guild's priorities for FT items are:<br>1. FT15 for clerics<br>2. FT15 for pure casters<br><br>This is subordinate to our RPP system (Raid Participation Point system), though. We are not going to hand FT items to people that have not spent time helping the guild raid.<br>&nbsp;<br>Forthoffer, 65/92 cleric, The Shadow Order, Lanys T'Vyl</td></tr>
